          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Main set of deflector plates sweeps the beam in a",
                "horizontal plane at 10 MHz and another set sweeps it",
                "in a vertical plane at 5 MHz. Beam bursts of duration",
                "less than one nsec. The average current is about 20 nA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " NE213 liquid scintillator, 2.5 cm thick and",
                "25 cm in diameter, was used for neutron detection. This",
                "is coupled with two XP1040 photomultiplier tubes.",
                "A second time-of-flight spectrometer using a 12.5 cm",
                "diameter scintillator is used to provide the monitoring",
                "for the experiments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Gas targets were used. The main section of target",
                "assembly was made from stainless steel tubing 2.25 cm",
                "in diameter. Into this tube slip in two 1.9 cm diameter",
                "tubes through O ring seals. One end of a \"slip-in\" tube",
                "was open while an aperture was mounted on the other",
                "end. A nickel foil was soldered on this aperture. The",
                "stopping power of the nickel foil was about 80 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
